{"ts":"2026-07-09T10:33:07.477Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-2ldo"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"GH-485: pm search rewrites quoted status:all hybrid queries into --status and drops keywords"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"Quoted hybrid queries beginning with an inline status: filter are rewritten into a --status flag whose value swallows the remaining keywords, leaving no positional keywords and failing the command. Reproduced on 2026.7.9."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Issue"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":2},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["agent-ux","area:search","cli","gh-issue","parser"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-07-09T10:33:07.477Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-09T10:33:07.477Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"maintainer-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/acceptance_criteria","value":"pm search \"status:all scene grounding\" applies the status filter and treats remaining tokens as keywords; regression test covers inline-filter-first quoted queries; if a query is inline-filter-only, the error names the inline-filter syntax rather than a generic missing-keywords message"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-ydp6"}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"8766781226c5eb5a5a479f402ba32690615b8fe09072919126e089f570bfde92","message":""}
{"ts":"2026-07-09T10:33:21.848Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"append","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/body","value":"## Reproduction (verified on 2026.7.9, local build)\n\n```bash\npm search \"status:all scene grounding\" --limit 5\n# Error: Missing required argument keywords\n# Recovery bundle shows: attempted_command: pm search --status \"all scene grounding\" --limit 5\n```\n\nThe inline-filter rewriter consumes everything after `status:` into the flag value instead of stopping at the first whitespace token boundary.\n\n## Impact\nBreaks the documented duplicate-check workflow (`pm search \"status:all <keywords>\"` before create) that agents use to avoid re-filing items. Workaround: pass `--status all` explicitly and keep keywords positional.\n\n## Upstream\nhttps://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/485 (filed 2026-07-08 by unbraind while implementing an all-status duplicate-check workflow).\n\n## Likely surface\nInline query-syntax parser from GH-157 remainder work (pm-ldr1) — the `status:`/`tag:` token rewrite path in search argument normalization."},{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-09T10:33:21.848Z"}],"before_hash":"8766781226c5eb5a5a479f402ba32690615b8fe09072919126e089f570bfde92","after_hash":"4bf7b132dc4e992497814bb52536589de862e636330fa14d8b07963b048e0460"}
